plan:
Update the aggregate-output contention logic in `core/src/exec.rs` to split the retained-byte cap evenly between stdout and stderr instead of biasing toward stderr, while leaving `ExecCapturePolicy::retained_bytes_cap` unchanged. Then update the one coupled contention test in `core/src/exec_tests.rs` so its name and expected `stdout_cap`/`stderr_cap` reflect a 50/50 split; other aggregate-output tests remain valid and need no edits.

### EDIT 1
- file: `core/src/exec.rs`
- where: `aggregate_output (~890)` — change contention split from stdout minority share to even half-and-half
```old
    // Under contention, reserve 1/3 for stdout and 2/3 for stderr; rebalance unused stderr to stdout.
    let want_stdout = stdout.text.len().min(max_bytes / 3);
    let want_stderr = stderr.text.len();
    let stderr_take = want_stderr.min(max_bytes.saturating_sub(want_stdout));
    let remaining = max_bytes.saturating_sub(want_stdout + stderr_take);
    let stdout_take = want_stdout + remaining.min(stdout.text.len().saturating_sub(want_stdout));

    aggregated.extend_from_slice(&stdout.text[..stdout_take]);
```
```new
    // Under contention, reserve half for stdout and half for stderr; rebalance unused stderr to stdout.
    let want_stdout = stdout.text.len().min(max_bytes / 2);
    let want_stderr = stderr.text.len();
    let stderr_take = want_stderr.min(max_bytes.saturating_sub(want_stdout));
    let remaining = max_bytes.saturating_sub(want_stdout + stderr_take);
    let stdout_take = want_stdout + remaining.min(stdout.text.len().saturating_sub(want_stdout));

    aggregated.extend_from_slice(&stdout.text[..stdout_take]);
```

